==Characteristics of Saiun==
* Does '''NOT''' participate in Aerial Combat.
* Increases the chance for [[Aerial_Combat#Contact|Contact]].
* Prevents T-cross disadvantage ("Red T").
** In PvP, Saiun must be equipped in the '''player's fleet''' to cancel Red T. Saiun equipped on an opposing player's fleet will '''NOT''' cancel Red T.<ref>[http://imgur.com/aBIWxPi Admiral Mikado's KCV screenshot of Red T formation with opponent's Hiyou equipping a Saiun.]</ref>
* Does '''NOT '''prevent Red T in Aerial Combat nodes.
** While it doesn't prevent Red-T on aerial nodes, it is irrelevant as airstrikes are unaffected by engagement modifiers.

|trivia = 
The development of carrier-based reconnaissance aircraft wasn't something contemplated even prior to the opening of World War II, this was mostly due to the limited plane capacity that Carriers had, thus the role of reconnaissance was delegated to fighters or torpedo bombers. Prior to the Attack on Pearl Harbor and the Battle of Midway, the IJN mainly relied on its seaplanes launched from its battleships and cruisers.
*Ironically, despite its high speed over fighter interception, it was the last aircraft shot down in the war, Japanese surrender happening just 5 minutes later.

